overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetic
  appeal of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was
  functional but visually uninspired. The assistant conducted a detailed review
  of the existing design, identifying issues such as a generic color palette,
  plain backgrounds, dense form sections, and a lack of visual personality. The
  approach involved a systematic overhaul, starting with a new calming,
  sleep-themed color palette (indigo/purple with teal accents). Key components
  like the main questionnaire form, progress bar, introduction section, and
  various form fields (checkboxes, radio groups, sliders) were redesigned. The
  goal was to create a more nuanced, trustworthy, and engaging interface that
  resonates with users seeking sleep insights, resulting in a polished and
  professional application.
